side works by Maggie Anderson, doris davenport, Jeff Mann, Lisa Alther, Julia Watts, Fenton Johnson, and Silas House, as well as filmmaker Beth Stephens. While primarily focused on 1976 to 2020, Doubly Erased also looks back to the region's literary "elders," thoughtfully mapping the place of sexuality in the lives and works of George Scarbrough, Byron Herbert Reece, and James Still.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican literaturezAppalachian RegionxHistory and criticism. 0aMountain life in literature. 0aSexual minorities in literature. 0aSexual minoritieszAppalachian RegionxIntellectual life. 0aSexual minorities' writings, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aLiterature : American Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / LGBT.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849357240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493572/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles